              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(figurative extension of meaning of {L:σκότος&lt;SDBG:σκότος:000000&gt;}[a] ‘darkness,’ {D:14.53}) the realm of sin and evil</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>evil world</Gloss>
                <Gloss>realm of evil</Gloss>
                <Gloss>darkness</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is possible that in {S:05100101300016} σκότος[b] is a figurative reference to the Devil or Satan, since ἐκ τῆς ἐξουσίας τοῦ σκότους is in a parallel relationship with τὴν βασιλείαν τοῦ υἱοῦ τῆς ἀγάπης αὐτοῦ.</Comments>
